reviewer_comment:
**Issue:** The `Default()` method assigns a shared pointer to the `Time` field of every `RuntimePatch`, which can lead to unintended side effects if any part of the system mutates this shared time value.

**Why it matters:** This approach introduces potential bugs and inconsistencies, particularly in concurrent environments or when multiple patches are being updated independently. It violates the principle of data isolation and can lead to hard-to-detect issues.

**Severity:** High

**Category:** Reliability

**Suggestion:** Create a new `metav1.Time` instance for each patch to ensure they do not share a pointer. Here is a revised version of the code:

```go
func (p *PlainML) Default(ctx context.Context, oldObj, newObj *trainer.TrainJob) error {
	now := metav1.Now()

	if oldObj == nil {
		for i := range newObj.Spec.RuntimePatches {
			newObj.Spec.RuntimePatches[i].Time = &metav1.Time{Time: now.Time} // Create a new copy
		}
	}
	return nil
}
```

