reviewer_comment:
**Issue:** The current implementation leaves the `Time` field unset when an unchanged patch has `old.Time == nil`.

**Why it matters:** This can lead to inconsistent behavior where some patches have a `Time` field and others do not, making it harder to rely on the presence of this field for all patches.

**Severity:** Medium

**Category:** Reliability

**Suggestion:**
```go
if old.Time != nil {
	patch.Time = old.Time
} else {
	patch.Time = &now
}
```

This ensures that `Time` is always set, which can help maintain consistency and reliability in the system.

