**Issue:** The current implementation does not ensure that the underlying JobSet/Pods are terminated when `ActiveDeadlineSeconds` is exceeded. Instead, it only sets a failure condition and short-circuits future reconciles as "finished", allowing the workload to continue running.

**Why it matters:** This can lead to resource leaks, increased costs, and potential data corruption or inconsistencies due to prolonged execution of the train job after its deadline has been reached.

**Severity:** High

**Category:** Reliability

**Suggestion:** Modify the `reconcileDeadline` function to delete/terminate the owned JobSet (or otherwise stop runtime resources) before marking the TrainJob finished. Ensure a reconcile path continues until termination is observed.

Example code snippet:

```go
func (r *TrainJobReconciler) reconcileDeadline(ctx context.Context, trainJob *trainer.TrainJob) (ctrl.Result, error) {
	if trainJob.Spec.ActiveDeadlineSeconds == nil || trainjob.IsTrainJobFinished(trainJob) || ptr.Deref(trainJob.Spec.Suspend, false) {
		return ctrl.Result{}, nil
	}
	startTime := trainJob.CreationTimestamp.Time
	if resumedCond := meta.FindStatusCondition(trainJob.Status.Conditions, trainer.TrainJobSuspended); resumedCond != nil && resumedCond.Status == metav1.ConditionFalse {
		startTime = resumedCond.LastTransitionTime.Time
	}
	if startTime.IsZero() {
		return ctrl.Result{}, nil
	}
	deadline := startTime.Add(time.Duration(*trainJob.Spec.ActiveDeadlineSeconds) * time.Second)
	if time.Now().After(deadline) {
		setFailedCondition(trainJob, constants.TrainJobDeadlineExceededMessage, trainer.TrainJobDeadlineExceededReason)

        // Add code to delete/terminate the owned JobSet/Pods
        jobSets := &trainer.JobSetList{}
        if err := r.client.List(ctx, jobSets, client.InNamespace(trainJob.Namespace), client.MatchingLabels(trainJob.Labels)); err != nil {
            return ctrl.Result{}, err
        }
        for _, jobSet := range jobSets.Items {
            if err := r.client.Delete(ctx, &jobSet); err != nil {
                return ctrl.Result{}, err
            }
        }

		return ctrl.Result{}, nil
	}
    ...
}
```

This modification ensures that when the deadline is exceeded, the underlying JobSet and Pods are properly terminated before marking the TrainJob as failed. This prevents resource leaks and maintains the integrity of the system.

