**Issue:** The current logic for handling the deadline and status update in `Reconcile` function does not correctly handle the requeue after time.

**Why it matters:** If `deadlineResult.RequeueAfter` is greater than zero, the controller should return immediately without applying any updates. However, if there is an error during the deadline reconciliation, the status update logic might be executed even though no actual change was made to the status.

**Severity:** high

**Category:** reliability

**Suggestion:**
```go
	if deadlineResult, deadlineErr := r.reconcileDeadline(ctx, &trainJob); deadlineErr != nil || deadlineResult.RequeueAfter > 0 {
		if deadlineErr != nil {
			err = errors.Join(err, deadlineErr)
		}
		if deadlineResult.RequeueAfter > 0 {
			return deadlineResult, err
		}
		return deadlineResult, errors.Join(err, r.client.Status().Patch(ctx, &trainJob, client.MergeFrom(prevTrainJob)))
	}
```

This suggestion ensures that if `deadlineResult.RequeueAfter` is greater than zero, the function returns immediately without applying any updates. If there is an error during the deadline reconciliation and a requeue is not required, the status update logic will be executed correctly.

